crab-certbundle (0.4.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * 0.4.2 release: declarative PKI and config template commands.
    - crabctl pki build: create a root CA, intermediates, and leaf certs
      from a single pki.yaml file; idempotent, supports --dry-run and
      --force-certs
    - crabctl pki init-config: generate an annotated pki.yaml template
    - crabctl init-config: generate a crab.yaml template (--minimal / full)

 -- snafus <snafus@users.noreply.github.com>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

crab-certbundle (0.4.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * 0.4.1 bug-fix release.
    - validate: fix NotADirectoryError crash on bundle/pkcs12 output paths;
      non-directory profiles now skipped with explanatory message (#4)
    - output: fix trailing slash in output_path corrupting staging and backup
      paths (OSError EINVAL / FileNotFoundError on os.rename); normalise
      output_path and staging_path with os.path.normpath at construction (#5)

 -- snafus <snafus@users.noreply.github.com>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

crab-certbundle (0.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * 0.4.0 release: certificate lifecycle commands.
    - cert renew: revoke-and-reissue using parameters from existing cert;
      --days, --reuse-key, --force; atomic-safe (issue before revoke)
    - cert sign --csr: CSR-based issuance; private key never enters CRAB
    - Fix: renew_cert revoke-before-issue ordering (data-loss risk)
    - Fix: cert_renew CLI datetime compat with cryptography >= 42

 -- snafus <snafus@users.noreply.github.com>  Fri, 17 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

crab-certbundle (0.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * 0.3.0 release: operational observability milestone.
    - crabctl status: cert counts, expiry, CRL freshness, last-built time; --json
    - --log-format json: structured JSON logging (one object per line); also
      configurable via logging.format in crab.yaml
    - --strict-warnings on build/refresh: exits 3 on policy WARN or CRL failures
    - Parallel CRL fetching (ThreadPoolExecutor, max_workers configurable)
    - 749 tests passing across EL8/EL9, Ubuntu 22.04/24.04

 -- snafus <snafus@users.noreply.github.com>  Thu, 16 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

